Mainly, my idea was/is to have a small group of higher level chars, (25+ prolly) of every class (if possible). These people will act as Big Brothers/Sisters to various newbies of the same class. Now, first question: No, its not powerleveling. Both parties need to understand that from the begining. The high level should not interfere directly with the whole newbie process of rat killing and running from big mean pumas <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . If the newbie is about to die and they just leveld again for the 3rd time or something of that nature, then yeah you can step in..thats just being generaly nice. <br>
As this is not powerleveling, its not truly required to even be in the same zone. Mainly the Big Brother provides a few things. <br>
1)Training and knowledge gained from experiance on how to play their shared class. This can be anything and everything, from mage pet use, Necro fear kiting, druid kiting, warrior taunting, monk equipment use, evil class/race faction tips, etc etc etc etc.<br>
2)A friend and future ally. This newbie will be level 60 someday, most likely. and if you are still playing, then thats one more level 60 you can most likely count on for Veeshan's Peak.<br>
Also, the higher level can provide a sounding board and faq for the newbies on stuff like quests and faction and the bazaars, and just generally be a friend. <br>
<br>
Now, there are a few problems that could pop up. <br>
1)This is not aimed at the level 3 mage from a guy that also plays a level 45 warrior, since the guy behind the keyboard most likely knows most of the stuff we can teach him, at least the really basic newbie stuff. All we can provide to him is the same thing 50 mage specific sites provide. <br>
2)A seperate website will prolly need to be created to hold a submit area for newbies who want to join, lists of the higher level chars of each class, maybe screen archives, news..etc etc..short of like a mini-guild website. <br>
3)The program needs a seperate director to monitor what Big brother goes to what newbie, monitor submissions, maintain the page, etc etc. This could be both an easy or difficult job, depending on the person. <br>
<br>
Over all though, I think this could really give newbies a real nice outlook on this game from the get go, and maybe soften some of our 30+ cynic player hearts <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
