<br>
I think the people that want to know the Answers are the ones that ask the questions. They don't know when they will need to ask any questions or when they will have problems. So it's hard to set a day. &quot;Okay you level one warrior you can only ask me questions at this date and at this time.&quot; Of course the flip side is you don't want to be flooded with questions when your fighting lady Vox. (Which has happened to me. Heyyy maybe that's why I died. Yeah I'll blame the newbie.)<br>
<br>
What I usually also do, is if I'm in a newbie zone and I have a couple of Gaint Snake Fangs or some other low level item that rogues can use I look for newbie rogue and give it to them and then give them some tips. &quot;And If you ever need any help or have any questions give me a tell.&quot;  Works great. &lt;Grin&gt; I'm still a little worried that one deal all those people are going to take me up on that offer and I'll be sitting in Hate talking to newbies no stop. &lt;Snicker&gt; but we'll see.<br>
<br>
So in short, great idea but not sure how it's going to work. You can't really force people to ask you questions or for you to be around them until they do. &lt;Shrug&gt;<br>
